      • CycServerPool

        public CycServerPool(Collection<String> cycServersSpecs)
        Creates a Cyc server pool from provided collection of CycAddress string specifications.
        Parameters:
        cycServersSpecs - specification of a Cyc pool, listing servers in the following form: Collection { "host1:port1:c1", "host2:port2:c2", ... }, where hostX specifies the host name, portX specifies the network port, cX specifies the concurrency level - maximum number of concurrent jobs a Cyc server will allow. The cX parameter is optional and will default to 1 if absent.

      • CycServerPool

        public CycServerPool(String cycServersSpecs)
        Creates a Cyc server pool from provided string specification.
        Parameters:
        cycServersSpecs - specification of a Cyc pool, listing servers in the following form: "host1:port1:c1,host2:port2:c2,host3:port3:c2...", where hostX specifies the host name, portX specifies the network port, cX specifies the concurrency level - maximum number of concurrent jobs a Cyc server will allow. The cX parameter is optional and will default to 1 if absent.

                                                          int defaultConcurrencyLevel)
        Creates a CycServerPool for a set of CycAddresses, with a default concurrency level for each if unspecified in the original addresses. This method will not modify any of the original CycAddresses.
        Parameters:
        addresses - iterable group of CycAddresses from which to create the pool
        defaultConcurrencyLevel - the default concurrency level for each CycAddress, if unspecified
        Returns:
        a new CycServerPool
